<br>
Fighting vs a rogue, I'd do the same thing Waldena does, but if you can, Damage shield yourself before the fight (or during, if you get a chance). Rogues generally use very fast weapons, and a Damage shield can do some pretty useful damage, since you won't be able to dodge every shot. <br>
<br>
Think of a duel with a Rogue as a Pet Vs Rogue fight... Stay out of it as much as you can. The longer you can avoid the rogue for, the more your pet can wittle him/her down. I'd use a 54 water pet if you had it, or 52 Fire.. Earth pets are good too. <br>
<br>
Most rogues won't try to Instill Doubt, but if they do, they'll either chase you down (in which case just keep avoiding em till fear runs out), try to kill your pet (run in a different direction, make another pet), or apply a poison (nuke him! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ). It takes 10 seconds for a poison to be applied. <p><html>
